Exxaro Resources, the black-owned diversified resources business, has announced its intention to sell its 44% interest in New York Stock Exchange-listed Tronox, to focus on core activities.It said it intended to apply the proceeds from any future sales to, among other things, Exxaro&rsquo;s core operations and to fund capital commitments.The stake in Tronox, which is engaged in the mining, production and marketing of inorganic minerals and chemicals, is worth about $911m. It operates in more than 20 countries, including a mineral-sands mine in the Mtunzini wetlands in KwaZulu-Natal.Tronox&rsquo;s acquisition of titanium dioxide business Cristal for $1.673bn in cash and stock, would dilute Exxaro&rsquo;s interest to about 33%.